{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Chicken","content":["Place chicken into Varoma dish and fill chicken cavity with lemon and onion.","Place garlic, ginger, spring onions\/shallots and coriander into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add miso paste, soy sauce and mirin and mix <nobr>5 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Rub garlic ginger marinade all over chicken and set Varoma aside."]},{"title":"Broth","content":["Place onion and chilli into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Transfer into simmering basket and set aside.","Place mushrooms, oil, stock paste and water into mixing bowl and insert simmering basket with onion and chilli. Place Varoma with chicken into position and steam <nobr>45 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Add eggs to Varoma dish, arranging them around the chicken, then secure Varoma lid and steam <nobr>10-15 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>, or until chicken and eggs are cooked. Set Varoma aside and allow chicken and eggs to cool. Remove simmering basket with aid of spatula and discard contents.","Re-insert simmering basket, then weigh udon noodles into it and cook <nobr>1 min 30 sec\/100°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Remove simmering basket with aid of spatula, drain noodles, then divide between 4 serving bowls.","Re-insert simmering basket, then weigh carrot, corn and broccolini into it and cook <nobr>5-8 min\/100°C\/\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Remove simmering basket with aid of spatula, drain vegetables, then divide between the serving bowls placing over noodles. Season broth to taste with salt, then set aside to keep warm.","Shred reserved cooled chicken meat and discard carcass. Divide shredded chicken evenly between the serving bowls.","Peel reserved cooled eggs, cut each egg into halves and add 2 halves to each serving bowl. Pour broth into serving bowls, then garnish with spring onions\/shallots, coriander leaves, fried shallots and nori strips (optional). Serve immediately."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Chicken","content":["1 whole uncooked chicken (1.2-1.4 kg)","1 whole lemon, cut into halves","1 brown onion (approx.150 g), cut into quarters","3 garlic cloves","2 cm piece fresh ginger, peeled","3 spring onions\/shallots, trimmed and cut into quarters","3 sprigs fresh coriander, roots, stems and leaves","2 tbsp miso paste","2 tbsp soy sauce","1 tbsp mirin"]},{"title":"Broth","content":["1 brown onion (approx. 150 g), cut into halves","1 - 2 long red chillies, deseeded if preferred","3 - 4 dried shiitake mushrooms, sliced","1 tsp sesame oil","1 tbsp Chicken stock paste (see Tips)","1550 g water","4 whole eggs, washed","400 g udon noodles, rinsed and separated","120 g carrot (approx. 1-2 carrots), cut into halves lengthways and cut into slices (1 cm)","100 - 150 g canned baby corn, drained and cut into halves","150 - 200 g broccolini (approx. 1 bunch), trimmed and cut into pieces (4-5 cm)","1 - 2 tsp sea salt, to taste","1 - 2 spring onions\/shallots, trimmed and cut into thin slices, for garnishing","2 - 3 sprigs fresh coriander, leaves only, torn, for garnishing","1 tbsp fried shallots, for garnishing","1 nori sheet, cut into thin strips, for garnishing (optional)"]}],"id":"r83237","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/--V3kD7ihyfk\/XZM0abLixLI\/AAAAAAAAa8Q\/WV6cS05b0-EYVSpoOpIHFsOe-AXUQPQmACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_y5T-UPYdRs5A5Sfk.png","title":"Asian chicken noodle soup","publishedAt":"2015-05-15T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"86.3 g","fat":"45.5 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"38.1 g","calories":"3880 kJ \/ 923 kcal"},"usefulItems":"4 serving bowls","hintsAndTricks":["Please refer to <em>The Basic Cookbook <\/em>for the Chicken stock paste recipe."],"basicInfo":["medium","30m","1h 35m","4 portions"]}